President Obama will travel to Iowa on a three-day economic bus tour in the Midwest. He will host a town hall event in Decorah, IA and attend a Rural Economic Forum in Peosta, IA. The tour will also include events in Atkinson and Alpha, Illinois. The President aims to discuss ways to grow the economy, strengthen the middle class, and accelerate hiring. He will hear directly from Americans, including small business owners, local families, private sector leaders, rural organizations, and government officials. The goal is to promote economic growth, restore confidence in the nation's future, and enhance optimism for future generations.